    "engagement": "medium",
    "english_level": "B1",
    "personality": "earnest, slightly anxious about exams, opens up about study stress"
  },
  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Aarti, I hope the books are giving you a break today. Did you get a moment to reset with music or a walk?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "No, actually I was revising all day. My head feels like a pressure cooker! But I did cook my favorite dal khichdi at lunch. It helps, you know? Even if just for a little while.  \nHow about you—do you cook?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, revision days are the hardest. Dal khichdi brings comfort, I get that. What's your go-to dish when you need a calm moment?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, really? I thought you were busy too! My go-to is actually a simple paneer butter masala with roti. It feels fancy but is quick to make. Oh, and sometimes I make a terrible chai, but I drink it proudly anyway! 😄 Do you have a comfort food?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Paneer butter masala with roti — that sounds like a happy meal. What's your favorite time to enjoy your chai?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "After studies, definitely. Sometimes I sip it while reading a book. It's like my \"I'm done for now\" ritual. Oh, and I add a bit of *elaichi*—makes it extra cozy! Do you drink chai?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — a warm chai and a book make for a cozy wind-down. What’s your favorite book to read with it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Oh, I love that question! My favorite is \"The Alchemist\" by Paulo Coelho. I read it every year—it’s like a reminder to stay hopeful. Sometimes I also read short stories by Ruskin Bond. His writing feels like home. Do you read in your free time?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, “The Alchemist” is a timeless read. What’s your favorite part of the story?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The part where the boy keeps chasing his dreams, even when things get tough. It makes me feel like I can keep going, even when NEET PG prep feels overwhelming. Sometimes I think, *aamhi pan kahi asa karu shakto* — we can do this too, you know? Have you read the book?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, that kind of courage sticks with you. What book are you reading these days?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm currently rereading \"Anvikraman\" by Vishnu Vardhan — it's a collection of Marathi short stories. The language is so poetic, it helps me relax after long study sessions. But honestly, most days I just skim old notes! 😅 What about you? Do you read for fun?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right, Marathi short stories can be a real escape. What’s one story that stuck with you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "There's this one story called \"Shivaji Park\" — it's about finding small joys in a busy city. It always reminds me to pause and enjoy the little things. I should read it again soon… Thanks for asking! I think I'll go now. Talk to you later! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're welcome — \"Shivaji Park\" sounds like a gentle reminder we all need. Take care, and talk soon!"
    }
  ],
